Potamolepis Marshall, 1883
( Potamolepidae ) is an endemic Afrotropical genus ( Manconi & Pronzato 2002 ; Manconi & Pronzato 2009 ) comprising of seven valid species (see
Van Soest et al . 2019
):
P. leubnitziae Marshall, 1883
;
P. chartaria Marshall, 1883
;
P. pechueli Marshall, 1883
;
P. weltneri Moore, 1903
;
P. marshalli Burton, 1938
;
P. micropora Burton, 1938
and
P. belingana Levi, 1965
and has never been recorded from any other terrestrial realm ( Manconi & Pronzato 2002 ; 2009 ; Manconi et al . 2015).

