subSection.paragraph:
Spongillidae is cosmopolitan, while Metaniidae and Potamolepidae are circumtropical with a Gondwana origin ( Manconi & Pronzato 2007 ; 2015). Malawispongiidae on the other hand has a discontinuous distribution in ancient lakes ( Manconi & Pronzato 2007 ; 2015). It was found that the absence of gemmules restricted dispersal in the endemic lubomirskiid sponges from lake Baikal. Phylogenetic analysis indicates that spongillid lineages are sister groups to the several endemic freshwater sponge taxa (
Erpenbeck et al . 2011
). Thus, it is plausible that several endemic freshwater lineages arose from members of the widespread freshwater sponge Family Spongillidae .
